8d35d10d93adc057b78d7a97125b1538028094dd.commit.message:
[WSS-178] - A fix for "signature verification failure of signed saml token"
 - The problem was that the SAML Assertion was below the STR, which assumed the Assertion would always have been previously processed
 - Also fixed the "No message with ID..." exception that was being thrown in XML Security.
8d35d10d93adc057b78d7a97125b1538028094dd.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

85a245d9b92e20bd1cecc8f52b62141ee29ea27a.commit.message:
[WSS-179] - Added (better) support for signature using a symmetric key
 - Also removed wsu namespace from the STR by default
 - Removed wsse and ds namespace definititions froms the TransformationParameters
 - Removed UT_SIGNING configuration from WSSecSignature...the same functionality can be achieved using CUSTOM_SYMM_SIGNING
85a245d9b92e20bd1cecc8f52b62141ee29ea27a.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

b945d649b387101d08831c2981c0709e63c994a7.commit.message:
[WSS-177] - Added support for encryption using a symmetric key and EncryptedKeySHA1
 - Note that before the EncryptedKey data was always required to be inserted in the security header
 - Added some tests
 - Changed all encryption/signature parts to be a List rather than a Vector
 - Cached all calls to MessageDigest("SHA-1) to be static
b945d649b387101d08831c2981c0709e63c994a7.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

50bac01d6eeacf069f13009742774d7dcc7762bd.commit.message:
[WSS-40] - Some updates to the test keys + supporting multiple certificates in the processors
 - The SignatureProcessor now saves all X509Certs it finds in the WSSecurityEngineResult.
 - It also verifies all of them, not just the first one.
 - This caused some tests to fail, as the wss4j.keystore had out of date CA certs
 - I removed wss4j.keystore, and regenerated the wss40.jks keys/certs to meet the requirements.
 - Also added some tests for WSHandler.verifyTrust.
50bac01d6eeacf069f13009742774d7dcc7762bd.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

a20ad930ee807b5f4e7b3fd05b9e1e51eb250f15.commit.message:
Some BST processing optimisations
 - Removed unnecessary BinarySecurity construction in the BSTProcessor
 - Changed the SignatureProcessor to first ask the BSTProcessor for the certs...this should improve performance a good bit.
a20ad930ee807b5f4e7b3fd05b9e1e51eb250f15.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

ffc1567a6af2278da0988c3f98f936537b18ad78.commit.message:
Added a method to WSSecurityUtil to verify that required QName's are protected in the WSSecurityEngineResults according to a specified action
 - Added some tests as well.
ffc1567a6af2278da0988c3f98f936537b18ad78.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

9b6e2a9958d369bc75727a397a238836cc9a03d9.commit.message:
Some improvements to how we save results on protected elements
 - Removed WSDataRef#dataref...this wasn't being used properly anyway and is irrelevant to downstream processing.
 - Removed WSSecurityEngineResult TAG_SIGNED_ELEMENT_IDS and TAG_PROTECTED_ELEMENTS. These can be obtained from TAG_DATA_REF_URIS instead.
9b6e2a9958d369bc75727a397a238836cc9a03d9.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

eec2b9f7c060a138ef18d1176de72c6c039985a3.commit.message:
[WSS-147] - Added a "checkReceiverResultsAnyOrder" method to WSHandler.
 - Applications can use this instead of checkReceiverResults if they want...I'm not changing the Axis Handlers to use it though.
eec2b9f7c060a138ef18d1176de72c6c039985a3.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh
